ProtoTheorem:
. "The equation $x^2\equiv a\pmod{p}$ has no solution if and 
   only if $a^{(p-1)/2}\equiv -1\pmod{p}$. Thus 
   $\left(\frac{a}{p}\right) \equiv a^{(p-1)/2}\pmod{p}$."
